.TH XTATUSBAR 1 "JANUARY 2026" "1.0" "User Manuals"
.SH NAME
xtatusbar \- a highly configurable system status bar generator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xtatusbar
[\fB\-\-separator\fR \fISEP\fR] [\fIMODULE_OPTIONS\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B xtatusbar
collects information from various system sources (Battery, CPU, RAM, Volume, etc.) 
and outputs a formatted string. Each component can be enabled/disabled, timed, and 
re-patterned via command-line arguments.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-separator\fR \fISEP\fR
Sets the string used to separate components. Default is "|".
.SH MODULE OPTIONS
Each component (bat, script, cpu, ram, temp, disk, vol, net, date) supports the following flags:
.TP
\fB\-\-\fR[\fImodule\fR]\fB\-enabled\fR [\fItrue|false\fR]
Enable or disable the specific component.
.TP
\fB\-\-\fR[\fImodule\fR]\fB\-time\fR \fIMILLISECONDS\fR
Set the update interval in milliseconds.
.TP
\fB\-\-\fR[\fImodule\fR]\fB\-pattern\fR \fIPATTERN\fR
Set the format string (e.g., "CPU %d%%").
.TP
\fB\-\-\fR[\fImodule\fR]\fB\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Specify a custom sysfs path or script file (Available for: bat, script, temp).
.SH EXAMPLES
.B xtatusbar \-\-separator " :: " \-\-cpu\-pattern "LOAD %d" \-\-bat\-enabled false
.PP
This runs xtatusbar with a custom separator, changes the CPU format, and hides the battery.
